.
.
At night - a lonely figure wanders through the bushes by the lake, leaves and small twigs get caught in the matted fabric. In the semi-darkness of the full moon night you can see shadows and now and then you can see the fear-distorted eyes of this person. Looking around again and again, the figure, man or woman is difficult to recognize, comes to this tree, right on the lake. A bench hugs the wooden trunk. The wind has picked up a bit and the leaves rustle, the branches creak slightly. Suddenly you can see the man's face in the moonlight, it is an older man with deep furrows on his face. He wears a monk's habit. Again and again, looking around in fear, he sits down on the bench and tries to hide in the shade of the tree. He looks out over the Chiemsee, in the direction of the Fraueninsel, and allows himself a brief moment of calm. He closes his eyes, exhales heavily and does not notice the second person who is stepping behind him at this moment of calm.
